   Write a program that will calculate the sum of all lengths of the strings below and store the sum in variable ``sum_of_lengths``. Then find the average length of the strings and store it in ``average_length`` variable.
   ~~~~
   my_list = ["","hello","", "goodbye", "wonderful", "hello", "goodbye", "I love Python"]

   ====
   from unittest.gui import TestCaseGui
   import re
   class myTests(TestCaseGui):
       def testOne(self):
           self.assertEqual(sum_of_lengths, 46 , 'Checking the value of sum_of_lengths.')
       def testTwo(self):
           self.assertEqual(average_length, 5.75 , 'Checking the value of average_length.')
   myTests().main()
